<br>
Eli will group with good, evil and anything in between, as long as it benefits her at the end of the day. She doesn't fit neatly into either category, I guess she's chaotic neutral really.<br>
<br>
Likewise, I don't have a problem with an evil character who'll kill that druid before they have time to protest &quot;But... I'm evil!&quot;<br>
If they want to play a character who wouldn't accept that typically good races can have a change of heart, then that's the character they're playing.<br>
<br>
That said I do think that at the end of the day, RL comes first and if I were playing an evil character and a good character really needed my help, I would probably drop RP for a short time to help them. PoEli doesn't want to see anyone in RL having a hard time, I know how stressful this game can get.<br>
