<br>
And No, I don't play my druid as evil or anything, but she is neutral, which follows my general, personal ideal of what a druid is. I just think too many people make assumptions that everyone plays strictly to the backstory, and that they need to be more flexible to this.<br>
<br>
And yes, a guild can enforce those restrictions, if they like, doesn't mean I have to agree with it or like it. Hopefully none of the people I like interacting with ever join one of these guilds. One of my guild members does RP this way, but I am not forced to play this way, and only do when she is grouped with me out of consideration for her RP.<br>
<br>
So I don't go telling her either how she should RP.<br>
<br>
You used the wrong terminology for what I was trying to do here. :P<br>
