<br>
Yes, EQ has a backstory, races are set and created with a clear history, same with classes. But then, just because I choose to play a dark elf, does that mean I have to play just another mindless automaton that hates everybody because the god, and SOE, says so? Wow... that would be some amazing RP...<br>
<br>
Dark elf says to high elf: &quot;I hate you!&quot;<br>
<br>
High elf groans and mutters: &quot;didn't we just have this conversation 5 minutes ago? No, wait, that was another dark elf. Hmmm.. that would mean the one before could have been a different one... and the one before them, and before them... Goddess Tunare, are you all robots?!&quot;<br>
<br>
BORING!<br>
<br>
Are humans the only race that can have diversity? Can only humans range from good to evil? Why must every other race be shoved into tight RP boxes? Yes, dark elves, as a whole, are evil because of the society in which they live, yet it is really that hard to grasp that one or two may seek redemption? After all, Innoruuk just twisted and perverted them, but, from what I have read and seen, Tunare is actually their creator goddess.<br>
<br>
Sorry, I personally will never play just another cog in the wheel, I like to think my imagination goes a little beyond that. I have played Vivienne as a cruel, immoral b**ch, but also loves her family, and would defend to the death those that she cares about. No one in the real world is flat and two-dimensional, why should the characters that we create and portray be the same?<br>
<br>
As for Jaranna's statement, she has every right to wish to group with others, good or evil. It is a choice that she should be able to make for RP reasons, and not be forced by unrealistic circumstances within the game's programming that has nothing to do with RP (Big Brother says you can NOT group with that dark elf because Big Brother has deemed them EVIL, and all exactly the same!). <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.shaw.ca/baddog117/vivirose.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
